   This is the variational origin of the \phi factor that appears in the final field equation.
2.2 Derivation of the Conformal Metric
The Conformal Relation linking the scalar field to the geometry is derived by demanding that the total informational capacity of any volume V remains invariant under a change in \mathcal{S}.
 * Informational Capacity: The informational capacity I is proportional to the geometric volume in Planck units: I \propto V / \ell_{\text{P}}^4.
 * Invariance: Demanding \delta I = 0 for a small change \delta \mathcal{S} implies that the determinant of the metric must be a simple function of the \mathcal{S} field.
 * Metric Derivation: The solution that maintains causality and recovers the linear weak-field limit is the exponential map:
   This rigorously establishes that the \mathcal{S} field acts as the conformal factor for the emergent spacetime geometry.
